<br>
do i think this is fair <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> at this point in time of the game</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->?<br>
<br>
yes.<br>
<br>
consider this:<br>
druids dont nuke as well as us early on, because they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> heal better</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> relative to other healing classes. so for balance, their offense is less relative to other offensive classes.<br>
<br>
however, 50+ druid healing ability stagnates. for balance they receive an upgrade in their damage dealing capabilities so they dont become underpowered.<br>
<br>
notice he said they will be looking at priests after they do pets. if druids become relatively powerful healers again, and mages still do less dd damage than druids, ill agree with the collective mage opinion on this matter, yes it will then be wrong they nuke better if they also heal very well. <br>
although i doubt it will happen like that. what i think will happen is druids will become more powerful healers again after the priest balancing, and then when they look at pure casters they will upgrade sofb so that it is more powerful than moonfire (think lava bolt vs starfire). <br>
<br>
everyone will be happy.<br>
the collective druid opinion is they want to heal/support first, and be offense second. it will be terrific if they recieve better heals.<br>
<br>
the collective mage opinion is they prefer being the second best nukers, and taking an offensive role. it will be terrific if pets get upgraded some more, and sofb is also upgraded.<br>
<br>
both classes will get what they want. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330" target="new"><b>Noonie Violetskies</b>, 58 High Elven Conjurer</a> <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61427" target="new"><b>Aylliah Ravenlure</b>, 45 Erudite Enchantress<br></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucolleen2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Colleen2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 5:46:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=223.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/colleenmage/eye.txt WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heads up! From graffe's</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure what he's talking about will be making pets neutral to mobs and npcs, if they planned to up their combat ability in any other way, it would have already been done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udevictionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DevictionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 6:07:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=223.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heads up! From graffe's</span><hr size=1> christ can we please leave this thread on topic?  NO HIJACKING.   No druid damage vs. Mage damage bs.<br>
