<br>
I'm of course very enthusiastic that pet changes are coming up next. Things previously mentioned as possibilities are more hps, more ATK, better saves, and the possibilities of nuetral pets. Whatever they go live with I feel better about possible changes now than ever before in EQ, and if we don't get it all of the changes I'm more likely to be ok with it because I feel that the changes that have been made of late have been better informed decisions than in the past.<br>
<br>
While I'm as impatient for class changes as any other mage, I feel like the wait may finally be worthwhile. I compare this to the discussions that took place about class balance over a year ago that caused me to leave the magician class for nearly 6 months. I'm glad I'm back, and optimistic about the direction things are moving. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
